        public static DByte constructFromUByteArr(UByte[] uByteArr)
        Returns a new DByte object from the clone of the given UByte array. If the array size is less than 2, new UBytes with value zero will be added on the right, and if it has more than 2 UButes, the first 2 will be picked.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        a new DByte object

      • constructFromBinStr

        public static DByte constructFromBinStr(java.lang.String binStr)
        Returns a new DByte object from the given binary string. If the string size is less than 16, it will be right-padded with 0's. If it has more than 16 binary digits, the digits after 16 will be truncated. The string might contain underscores/spaces for readability purpose.
        Parameters:
        binStr - the given string of binary digits
        Returns:
        a new DByte object
